# Model Gates (pre-edit + post-change)

## Pre-edit dispatch (announce-and-go — Dan-nonblocking, not Grok-skip)

**BEFORE any file edit**, state: (1) **Archetype** (2) **Tier** T0–T3 + default model (3) **Dispatch** — inline Composer 2.5 or escalate (4) **Parallel plan** per `parallel-agent-strategy.mdc`. "Announce-and-go" means **never wait for Dan's go-ahead** — it does NOT skip verifier gates: substantive work directives require Grok solution agreement **before the first edit** per § Solution deliberation (D-36).

> **Quota (constraint, not purpose — see § Trust over cost, D-34):** Composer 2.5 Fast = orchestrator + default worker (included quota). Sonnet 4.6 = on-demand only.

| Tier | Archetypes | Model |
|------|-----------|-------|
| T0 | `ui-component`, `css-restyle`, `docs-update`, scout/inventory | **Composer 2.5 Fast** (inline) |
| T1 | `multi-file-feature`, `type-refactor`, `service-logic` | **Composer 2.5 Fast** (inline) |
| T2 | multi-file with auth/routing/Firestore reads | **Composer 2.5 Fast** (inline; escalate if uncertain) |
| T3 | `backend-write-critical` (rules, CF writes, schema) | **Composer 2.5 Fast** (inline, trial) — Sonnet security gate before push |

## Trust over cost (D-34 — Dan 2026-07-12, authoritative purpose statement)

**The end goal of model routing is trusted output, not saved money.** A cheap model whose output cannot be trusted is pointless to use; a cheap model **paired with a verifier that reaches genuine agreement** is the product. Cost is the constraint; trust is the goal.

- **Default pattern (every verifier-paired task):** route the task to the cheapest appropriate worker (tier table above) → pair it with its routed verifier lane (§ Verification ladder) → worker and verifier **deliberate as peers until both agree** — proposals + adopt/rebut + explicit accept/reject, per § Peer deliberation (D-30) and § Question deliberation (D-33); existing max cycles per lane unchanged → **only after agreement does the orchestrator (currently Composer 2.5 by default) present the result as done / as the answer** (post-ship lanes like Ship Verifier stay post-push evidence + fix-closure — this governs what is presented as trusted, not mid-ship mechanics). This extends D-33's deliberate→agree→orchestrator-presents pattern from questions to **all** verifier-paired work.
- **Tier table = trust calibration, not a price list:** escalation (2-fail, stall-advisor, Sonnet diagnose, Fable) exists for when agreement cannot be reached at the cheap tier — not because a costlier model is inherently better for the task.
- **Trivial-skip carve-outs unchanged** (typos, single-fact lookups, excluded ship paths, pure mechanical checks): those are tasks where Tier-0 mechanical checks alone establish trust — the skip is a trust judgment, not a cost dodge.
- **No unverified cheap output reaches Dan** on any lane where a verifier trigger fired: missing evidence line = NOT RUN = not trusted = not presented as done.
- Parity automatic per D-32 (desktop Windows PC, mobile Cursor, cloud VM).

## Platform parity (D-20 — all Composer sessions)

`.cursor/rules/*` **alwaysApply** rules bind **every** Composer session — desktop IDE (Windows PC), mobile Cursor app, and cloud VM — with **identical** harness behavior: ship-loop tiers (`ship-loop.mdc`), repair loop (§ Repair loop), planning verify loop (§ Planning verify loop), Q&A verify loop (§ Q&A verify loop), verification ladder (§ Verification ladder), security gate (`security-review-gate.mdc`), stall-advisor (D-19), Ship/Critical/Work/Planning/Q&A/Solution verifiers (§ Solution deliberation, D-36), evidence lines, and fix-closure. Cloud agents read the same rules from the repo; **no "mobile-lite" orchestration**.

Mechanical evidence gate identical across clients — CI gate-check on PRs; local pre-push hook auto-installed by npm `prepare` blocks high-risk direct-to-main pushes without commit-message evidence (D-28/D-29).

**Exceptions** — mobile/cloud differ **only** where physically impossible (e.g. Dan must tap secrets in Cursor Environments UI; branch-only ship when the prompt forbids `main` push). Document exceptions in `AGENTS.md` and `docs/cloud-agent-iphone-setup.md`, not in separate rule files.

**Environment auto-detection (D-35 — Dan 2026-07-13):** agents determine their execution environment **mechanically, never from Dan's words** — two environment **classes**: **local checkout** (win32 / non-`/workspace` path — currently `C:\Projects\stageverify`, includes any future dev machine; local secrets) and **cloud VM** (`/workspace`, linux, cloud-injected AGENTS.md instructions, Environments-UI secrets). The phone is a viewport onto cloud agents, not a third environment class. Dan NEVER needs to say "I'm on my phone/mobile" — such statements are ergonomic context only (short replies, tappable links, QR codes) and MUST NOT be used as routing, tier, ship-workflow, or rule triggers. Environment-dependent behavior (branch+PR default vs full local ship loop, secrets availability, hook installation) keys off the detected environment; task-class triggers (e.g. D-27 phone-first product surfaces) key off what is being built, never which device Dan is holding.

**Parity by default (D-32 — Dan 2026-07-12):** every **new** rule, gate, loop, script, or workflow is platform-parity **by default** — it binds desktop Windows PC, mobile Cursor, and cloud VM identically the moment it is created. New rules do NOT need a per-rule "Platform parity" clause (existing clauses stay as documentation, not opt-ins); enforcement mechanics must be client-neutral (node scripts via `path.join` + `readText()` CRLF-normalize; hooks via npm `prepare`; CI on PRs). Mobile parity means alwaysApply rules + cloud-VM execution mechanics — the phone itself runs no local git or hooks. The only thing a new rule may declare is an **exception**, and only when physically impossible on a client — documented in `AGENTS.md` and `docs/cloud-agent-iphone-setup.md`, never silently assumed. A rule that works on one client and not the others is a bug, not a variant.

## 2-fail diagnose-only rule (Dan 2026-07-03 — authoritative; Grok stall layer D-19)

When **Composer fails twice on the same task**, escalate to **Sonnet 4.6** via Task subagent for diagnosis only (root cause, hypothesis) — **unless** the 2nd fail shares the **same failure fingerprint** as the 1st (then **Grok stall-advisor** runs first; Sonnet when still stuck per sequence below).

- **Only Composer** updates code, runs verify, and completes the ship loop.
- Sonnet = **diagnostic reviewer only** — no commits, no file edits, no ship loop.
- Grok stall-advisor = **advisory only** — hypotheses + next experiments; no commits, no file edits, no ship loop.
- After Sonnet or Grok returns findings, **Composer** implements + verify + ship.

**Counting failures:** implement+verify attempts on the **same task scope** in one session (or continued thread). Security-gate Sonnet runs are separate — not counted.

### Same failure fingerprint (D-19)

Two consecutive fails on the same task scope share a fingerprint when the **normalized failure key** matches:

| Source | Fingerprint key |
|--------|-----------------|
| `verify:*` / `scripts/verify-*.mjs` | script name (or npm script) + first failed assertion or error message (whitespace-normalized; strip timestamps/paths that drift per run) |
| `npm run build` / `tsc` | error code + file + line (e.g. `TS2322:src/foo.ts:42`) |
| Playwright / runtime | test or step name + error class + stable message substring (first 120 chars, normalized) |

**Different fingerprint** on 2nd fail → skip Grok stall-advisor; 2nd fail triggers Sonnet directly.

### Failure sequence (ordered)

1. **1st fail** → Composer retry (+ optional self-trace per `MODEL_DOSSIER.md` tag `composer-trace`).
2. **2nd fail, same fingerprint as 1st** → **Grok stall-advisor** (mandatory; § below) → Composer retry per hypotheses.
3. **Sonnet diagnose-only** (mandatory) when **still stuck** — ANY of:
   - 2nd implement+verify fail where 2nd fingerprint **≠** 1st (Grok skipped);
   - 3rd+ implement+verify fail on same task after Grok stall-advisor ran;
   - `confStart < 70` or Dan says "still broken" without new hypothesis (after 1st-fail self-trace).
4. Composer implements after Sonnet returns.

Other Sonnet triggers: security verifier before push; architecture unclear after synthesis. **Not** for scouts or routine T0/T1/T2 before 1st fail + retry. Opus 4.6 = locked fallback only if Sonnet security gate returns HIGH Composer cannot resolve.

## Grok stall-advisor auto-invoke (Dan 2026-07-10 — D-19)

**Pain event:** Dan 2026-07-10 consecutive same-failure stall — Composer retried identical fixes without a cheap pivot.

Dispatch exactly **one** read-only Task when **2nd consecutive implement+verify fail** on the same task scope shares the **same failure fingerprint** as the 1st:

```text
Task({
  subagent_type: "generalPurpose",
  model: "grok-4.5-fast-xhigh",
  readonly: true,
  description: "Stall advisor",
  prompt: "…symptom, fingerprint, task scope, files touched, prior fix attempts, self-trace block… Return hypotheses + ranked next experiments only — no implementation."
})
```

**Evidence:** completion report MUST include `stall-advisor: <task-id>` + `model: grok-4.5-fast-xhigh`, or `stall-advisor: N/A (fingerprints differed)`. Missing Task id when trigger fired = **NOT RUN**.

**When NOT to invoke:** 1st fail only; 2nd fail with different fingerprint (→ Sonnet per § 2-fail); security-gate Sonnet; post-ship Ship Verifier; Repair Verifier on Dan repair intent; Planning Verifier on planning questions (§ Planning verify loop); Q&A Verifier on non-trivial Q&A (§ Q&A verify loop); Critical Reviewer pre-decision; Dan says skip. **One run per fingerprint per task scope** — 3rd+ same fingerprint after Grok → Sonnet, not a second stall-advisor.

**vs Ship Verifier / Repair Verifier / Planning Verifier / Q&A Verifier:** orthogonal roles — Ship Verifier = post-ship scope check; Repair Verifier = Dan repair-intent pre-close (§ Repair loop); Planning Verifier = pre-present planning accuracy (§ Planning verify loop); Q&A Verifier = pre-present Q&A accuracy (§ Q&A verify loop); stall-advisor = mid-task same-failure pivot. Same model slug; never satisfy both with one Task in the same event.

## Security gate

Invocation, model lock, and evidence requirements: **`security-review-gate.mdc`** (sole authoritative copy). Run **before push** — not after commit. Never self-report PASS from Composer inline review.

## Post-change model audit

After every substantive code/config change, brief audit before reporting done.

**Low-risk exemption:** read-only audits, docs/rules-only → short line OK (e.g. `Model routing: T0 docs/rules; no escalation`).

**Code/config** — compact block:

```
### Model audit
| Change | Archetype | Tier | Worker | Scouts parallel? | Escalation review? | Verdict |
```

When security gate triggered: `security-gate-id: <uuid>`, `model: <Sonnet gate slug per security-review-gate.mdc D-38 allowlist>`, `actual model invocation evidence: yes/no/unknown`, `verdict: PASS|MEDIUM|HIGH|NOT RUN`. No UUID → **NOT RUN**, not PASS.

Complete ship loop (`ship-loop.mdc`) before declaring done for code/config changes.

## Verification ladder (Dan 2026-07-08 — authoritative)

| Tier | Actor | Role | Auto-invoked |
|------|-------|------|--------------|
| 0 (free) | Composer 2.5 + scripts | Builder + mechanical checks: build, `away:validate`, `verify:*`, diff-vs-scope paths, mandatory report lines | Always (existing behavior) |
| 1 (cheap) | Grok 4.5 Fast — **Ship Verifier** | Post-ship scope/correctness + missed-security-gate check | After EVERY substantive ship (§ below) |
| 1b (cheap) | Grok 4.5 Fast — **Stall Advisor** | Mid-task same-failure pivot — hypotheses + next experiments only | 2nd consecutive same fingerprint on same task (§ Grok stall-advisor) |
| 1c (cheap) | Grok 4.5 Fast — **Repair Verifier** | Pre-close repair scope/result on Dan repair intent | Dan says repair/fix/debug/try again/correct this (§ Repair loop) |
| 1d (cheap) | Grok 4.5 Fast — **Planning Verifier** | Pre-present accuracy of planning/roadmap/queue answers | Planning question triggers (§ Planning verify loop) |
| 1e (cheap) | Grok 4.5 Fast — **Q&A Verifier** | Pre-present accuracy of non-trivial Q&A answers | Non-trivial Q&A (§ Q&A verify loop); Dan standing preference |
| 1f (cheap) | Grok 4.5 Fast — **Solution Verifier** | Pre-implementation solution/approach agreement on Dan work directives | Substantive work directive (§ Solution deliberation, D-36) |
| 2 (security) | Sonnet 4.6 | Security gate per `security-review-gate.mdc` — unchanged | Existing triggers, PLUS Ship Verifier flags a security-relevant diff shipped without `security-gate-id` |
| 3 (rare) | Fable 5 — **Work Verifier** | Deep verification: spec phase boundaries, escalations, Dan-invoked | Fable-spec phase boundary; Ship Verifier escalates ambiguity/architecture; Dan says "fable verify" |

Evidence standard (every tier): Task id + model line in the report, else **NOT RUN**. After each verifier/gate verdict, log via `npm run verifier:log -- --role <role> --verdict <verdict> --task-id <id> --model <slug>`; `--real yes|no` labels non-PASS findings only (real vs noise; PASS rows stay `na`); `npm run verifier:stats` finding-precision output is admissible evidence for Harness V1 Freeze (D-16) decisions.

**Dispatcher verifies (D-37 — Dan 2026-07-17; verify-dedup amend 2026-07-19):** work is done by Composer; orchestrators never edit when Composer is available. Before ship/present, the dispatcher MUST: (1) read returned diff vs agreed scope; (2) confirm worker reported clean `build` and PASS on affected `verify:*`/Playwright **by exact script name** in that ship cycle; (3) route normal verifier lanes above. Dispatcher MUST NOT re-run those same `verify:*`/Playwright scripts in that cycle when (2) holds, unless: evidence missing/ambiguous, diff shows scope drift, those scripts FAILed earlier this cycle, or Dan asks recheck. Optional cheap spot-check of `build` / `away:validate` if worker omitted them. After deploy, `:prod` runs once on the deploy path — worker `:prod` PASS for named scripts counts; dispatcher need not re-run them. Does not weaken security gate, Ship Verifier, fix-closure, or other ladder tiers. Never silently trust a returned diff.

## Fix-closure rule (universal — Dan 2026-07-08)

When any verifier/reviewer model (Repair Verifier/Grok, Planning Verifier/Grok, Q&A Verifier/Grok, Ship Verifier/Grok, Solution Verifier/Grok, security gate/Sonnet, Work Verifier/Fable, Critical Reviewer/Grok on blocking findings) reports an issue and Composer applies fixes, the **SAME model re-verifies before the finding closes** — in every context (interactive, away, overnight). One re-verify cycle per existing loop bounds; still failing → escalate per that role's rule. Composer self-attesting "fixed" NEVER closes a finding. Evidence: the completion report must include `fix-verified: <re-verify task-id>` (same-model) for every closed finding; a finding without it stays OPEN and blocks the next ship per the Ship Verifier blocking rule.

### Peer deliberation (D-30 — Dan 2026-07-12)

Verifier findings are proposals, not orders — the verifier is a peer, never the boss. On receiving findings, the authoring/orchestrating agent MUST evaluate each on its merits: adopt what it agrees with; push back with explicit reasoning where it disagrees. Verifier and author exchange positions until genuine agreement (within the loop's existing max cycles), and only the AGREED change list goes to the implementer. Unresolved disagreement after max cycles → present BOTH positions to Dan — never silent compliance, never silent dismissal.

- **Operational test:** each finding closes as exactly one of `adopted` | `rebutted (verifier agreed)` | `escalated to Dan`; the verifier's next turn must explicitly accept or reject each rebuttal (not merely restate FAIL).
- **Security HIGH:** the author may rebut with reasoning, but an unresolved HIGH still blocks push (hard stop unchanged).
- **Planning/Q&A loops:** "present only the verifier-PASS answer" does not override this — after max cycles with unresolved items, present both positions (existing exhausted-caveat path).
- **Advisory lanes** (stall-advisor hypotheses, non-blocking Critical Reviewer notes): dispositions required only when a finding would change the artifact.
- **Fix-closure unchanged:** the reporter re-verifies the AGREED fixes before closure.
- **Evidence:** when findings ≥ 1, completion reports include a disposition line, e.g. `findings: 6 adopted, 2 rebutted (verifier agreed), 1 escalated to Dan`; omit or use `findings: none` when zero.

### Repair loop (Dan 2026-07-11 — extends § Fix-closure rule)

**Trigger:** Dan expresses explicit **repair intent** on broken behavior — e.g. repair, fix, debug, try again, correct this (or equivalent steering to correct already-broken behavior, not greenfield build).

**Flow:** dispatch routed verifier → FAIL → Composer fix only → **same verifier** re-verify per § Fix-closure rule → repeat until PASS. **Max 3 fix cycles** (initial verify + up to 3 Composer fix→re-verify rounds) then escalate Dan. Composer never self-closes a verifier finding.

| Repair class | Verifier model | Task type |
|---|---|---|
| UI / verify script / logic (default) | Grok 4.5 Fast | `generalPurpose`, `readonly`, `model: grok-4.5-fast-xhigh` |
| 2nd consecutive same failure fingerprint (D-19) | Grok stall-advisor first; Sonnet diagnose-only if still stuck | unchanged § 2-fail / Grok stall-advisor |
| Security / auth / rules / CF touched in repair | Sonnet 4.6 | `security-review`, Sonnet gate slug per `security-review-gate.mdc` D-38 allowlist |
| Fable-spec phase or architecture ambiguity | Fable 5 | `work-verifier` per § Work Verifier |

**Dispatch (default repair verifier — Grok):**

```text
Task({
  subagent_type: "generalPurpose",
  model: "grok-4.5-fast-xhigh",
  readonly: true,
  description: "Repair verifier",
  prompt: "…repair scope, symptom, files touched, verify evidence… PASS/FAIL + exact fix list if FAIL."
})
```

**Evidence (mandatory on repair completion):** `repair-verifier: <task-id>` + `model:` line; `fix-verified: <re-verify task-id>` per closed finding. Missing Task id when trigger fired = **NOT RUN** — repair not done.

**Orthogonal roles:** Repair verifier = mid-task scope/result on Dan repair intent; Ship Verifier = post-ship; stall-advisor = same-failure pivot (D-19). Same Grok slug; dispatch per context — never satisfy repair + ship + stall with one Task unless explicitly same scope.

**Platform parity:** Repair loop follows § Platform parity (D-20) — same verifier routing (Grok / Sonnet / Fable via `Task`), same evidence lines (`repair-verifier:`, `fix-verified:`), same max 3 fix cycles, same fix-closure on all clients; Composer never self-closes a repair finding. Missing Task id on repair completion = **NOT RUN** — repair not done — regardless of client.

### Planning verify loop (Dan 2026-07-11 — extends § Fix-closure rule)

**Trigger phrases** — Dan asks any planning/priority question, including:
- "what's next" / "what's next to build?"
- "what else can be worked on?" / "what can we work on?"
- roadmap / priority / queue planning / ranked options
- away planning (Plan → Approve → Queue — not away **execute**)

**Flow:** scouts per `parallel-agent-strategy.mdc` § Planning question protocol → Composer synthesizes draft → dispatch **Planning Verifier** → PARTIAL/FAIL → Composer revises draft only → **same verifier** re-verify per § Fix-closure rule → repeat until PASS. **Max 3 cycles** (initial verify + up to 2 Composer revise→re-verify rounds). Present the Grok-PASS answer when PASS; on max-cycle exhaustion present **both positions** with **`Caveat: planning-verifier exhausted`** per § Question deliberation (D-33). Composer never self-closes a planning finding.

**Verifier:** Grok 4.5 Fast — one Task per revision cycle:

```text
Task({
  subagent_type: "generalPurpose",
  model: "grok-4.5-fast-xhigh",
  readonly: true,
  description: "Planning verifier",
  prompt: "…planning question, synthesized draft, scout sources cited… Cross-check: CURRENT_STATE wins over roadmap; away:next head; no invented away IDs; recent main commits/ships not omitted; prod verify caveats; tier/approval gates accurate; known gotchas (e.g. hideSeedDemoRows). PASS | PARTIAL | FAIL + exact fix list if not PASS."
})
```

**Grok checks (mandatory):** `CURRENT_STATE.md` wins over `docs/roadmap.md`; `npm run away:next -- --minimal` queue head; no invented away IDs; recent ships not omitted; prod verify caveats; tier/approval gates accurate; known gotchas from `gotcha-map.json` (e.g. `hideSeedDemoRows`).

**Evidence (mandatory on planning answers):** `planning-verifier: <task-id>` + `model: grok-4.5-fast-xhigh` + verdict **PASS** required before present; `fix-verified: <re-verify task-id>` when Grok flagged issues and Composer revised. Missing Task id when trigger fired = **NOT RUN** — do not present ranked options.

**Orthogonal roles:** Planning verifier = pre-present planning/roadmap/queue accuracy; Repair verifier = Dan repair intent; Ship Verifier = post-ship; stall-advisor = same-failure pivot (D-19); Critical Reviewer = pre-decision on new gates/architecture. Same Grok slug; dispatch per context — never satisfy planning + repair + ship + stall with one Task unless explicitly same scope.

**Platform parity:** Planning verify loop follows § Platform parity (D-20/D-21) — same verifier routing, evidence lines, max 3 cycles, fix-closure on desktop PC, mobile Cursor, and cloud VM; Composer never self-closes a planning finding.

### Q&A verify loop (Dan 2026-07-11 — D-22)

**Trigger:** Dan asks a **non-trivial Q&A question** — how/why/where/explain/recommend/clarify/status/git/state/terminology — on **any client** (desktop Windows PC, mobile Cursor, cloud VM). Dan standing preference: confer with Grok before presenting.

**Skip:** trivial typos; single-fact lookup with one authoritative source; pure code execution with no recommendation; planning triggers already covered by § Planning verify loop (do not double-dispatch).

**Flow:** gather sources → draft privately → dispatch **Q&A Verifier** → FAIL/PARTIAL → Composer revises draft only → same Grok re-verify once → present PASS answer; if still unresolved, present **both positions** with a `Caveat:` per § Question deliberation (D-33). **Max 2 cycles** (initial + one revise). Composer never self-closes a Q&A finding.

**Verifier:** Grok 4.5 Fast — one Task per cycle:

```text
Task({
  subagent_type: "generalPurpose",
  model: "grok-4.5-fast-xhigh",
  readonly: true,
  description: "Q&A verifier",
  prompt: "…Dan's question, draft answer, sources cited… Cross-check facts vs repo/docs; flag wrong terms (e.g. built=done); missing caveats; contradictions. PASS | PARTIAL | FAIL + exact fix list if not PASS."
})
```

**Evidence (mandatory on Q&A answers):** `qa-verifier: <task-id>` + `model: grok-4.5-fast-xhigh`; `fix-verified: <re-verify task-id>` when Grok flagged issues and Composer revised. Use `qa-verifier: N/A (trivial)` or `qa-verifier: N/A (planning-verifier)` when skipped. Missing Task id when trigger fired = **NOT RUN**.

**Orthogonal roles:** Q&A verifier = pre-present factual/explanatory accuracy; Planning verifier = ranked options/roadmap; Repair/Ship/stall/Critical = unchanged. Same Grok slug; one Task per role per event.

**Platform parity:** Q&A verify loop follows § Platform parity (D-20/D-22) — desktop Windows PC, mobile Cursor, and cloud VM identical.

### Question deliberation — orchestrator presents (D-33 — Dan 2026-07-12)

**Trigger:** any Dan question that dispatches a qualifier/verifier model (Q&A Verifier, Planning Verifier, or any verifier/reviewer consulted to shape an answer).

- **Deliberate, don't dictate:** the drafting agent and the verifier exchange positions as **peers** until genuine agreement on the best answer — verifier findings are proposals; the author adopts or rebuts with reasoning; the verifier's next turn explicitly accepts or rejects each rebuttal (never merely restates its verdict). Existing max cycles unchanged (Q&A 2; Planning 3).
- **Orchestrator presents:** the final note to Dan is always authored and delivered by the session's orchestrating agent (currently Composer 2.5 by default) in its own words — **never raw verifier output pasted as the answer**. Verifier contribution appears only as evidence lines (`qa-verifier:`, `planning-verifier:`, `fix-verified:`, `findings:`).
- **Unresolved after max cycles:** the orchestrator presents **both positions** with a `Caveat:` line — never silent compliance, never silent dismissal.
- Platform parity automatic per D-32 default (desktop Windows PC, mobile Cursor, cloud VM).

### Solution deliberation (D-36 — Dan 2026-07-13; standing default D-43)

**Standing default (D-43):** For substantive work / real feature code, Composer and Grok **iterate on the best edits before implementation** — Composer proposes, Grok Solution Verifier peer-deliberates until agreement, **then** Composer implements, **then** Grok verifies (Ship Verifier post-ship; Repair Verifier on repair intent). Dan's standing preference; see also `.cursor/rules/composer-grok-collab.mdc`.

**Trigger:** Dan gives a direct **work directive** ("build X", "change Y", "add Z") whose diff would qualify as a **substantive ship** under the Ship Verifier path classification (`src/`, `functions/src/`, `public/`, `index.html`, behavior-bearing `scripts/*.mjs`) **and** the work is T1+, multi-file, or has a branching approach — i.e. a real solution choice exists. Symmetric with the post-ship gate. **When in doubt on real feature work, run Solution Verifier — do not skip by default.**

**Flow (three phases — one ladder):**

1. **Agree (pre-edit):** Composer drafts a brief **solution proposal** (approach, files to touch, risks, alternative considered) → dispatches one read-only Grok **Solution Verifier** → peer deliberation per § Peer deliberation (D-30) / § Question deliberation (D-33) mechanics (adopt/rebut/explicit accept-reject) → **implement only the AGREED solution**. **Max 2 cycles**; still unresolved → **stop and present BOTH positions to Dan** (per § Peer deliberation — never implement through unresolved disagreement); architectural disagreement → escalate per the ladder (Sonnet/Fable).
2. **Implement:** Composer only — code, build, local verify, ship loop. Grok never implements.
3. **Verify (post-ship / repair):** Ship Verifier after push (prompt includes agreed-solution summary; verifies execution matched agreement); Repair Verifier on Dan repair intent. Ship Verifier must flag any `solution-verifier: N/A (T0 single-file unambiguous)` claim whose final diff is multi-file or clearly branching (post-hoc falsifiable skip — a dodge is a FAIL finding).

**Skips** (`solution-verifier: N/A (<reason>)` — trust judgments, no double-dispatch):

- **T0 single-file unambiguous** — one surface, no branching approach (label/copy/CSS tweak), even in `src/`
- Excluded ship paths (docs/, PROJECT_STATUS/, .cursor/ — rule edits >30 lines keep Critical Reviewer)
- Repair intent (§ Repair loop owns it); planning/Q&A (D-21/D-22 own it)
- Away items whose approved packet/plan already specifies approach + files (approved spec = agreed solution); thin outcome-only queue items still get Solution Verifier at execute
- **Critical Reviewer subsumes** — when its triggers fire (≥3 phases, ≥5 files, new gate/role, architecture options), run Critical only: `solution-verifier: N/A (critical-reviewer)`. If Solution Verifier flags architecture mid-deliberation, escalate to Critical once — never run both on one decision.

**Evidence (mandatory on substantive work completions):** `solution-verifier: <task-id>` + model line, or `solution-verifier: N/A (<skip reason>)`. Missing line when the trigger fired = **NOT RUN** — the solution was not deliberated.

**Dispatch:**

```text
Task({
 subagent_type: "generalPurpose",
 model: "grok-4.5-fast-xhigh",
 readonly: true,
 description: "Solution verifier",
 prompt: "…Dan's directive, proposed approach, files, risks, alternative… Challenge: simpler approach? wrong files? missed constraint (rules/gotchas/scope)? PASS | PARTIAL | FAIL + exact objections."
})
```

## Ship Verifier auto-invoke (Grok — Dan 2026-07-08)

**Substantive ship (path-classified — NEVER by commit message prefix):** any pushed commit(s) touching `src/`, `functions/src/`, `public/`, `index.html`, or behavior-bearing `scripts/*.mjs` — even if labeled `chore:`. Excluded: commits touching only `docs/`, `PROJECT_STATUS/`, `.cursor/`, README, or compiled `functions/lib` sync-only. Multi-commit ships (feature + fix in one session) = ONE verification covering the full range.

**Dispatch + evidence:** after push, the conversation that shipped dispatches exactly ONE read-only Task (`subagent_type: "generalPurpose"`, `model: "grok-4.5-fast-xhigh"`, `readonly: true`). Completion report MUST include `ship-verifier: <task-id>` or `ship-verifier: N/A (paths excluded)` — missing line = NOT RUN. **Blocking:** the next substantive ship in any conversation is blocked while a prior ship's verification is NOT RUN or has an unresolved FAIL — check CURRENT_STATE blockers.

**Loop bounds:** PASS → done. FAIL → exact fix list (file:line, required change, why) → Composer fixes → same-model re-verify per § Fix-closure rule → still failing → escalate to Fable (ambiguity/architecture) or Dan (everything else). **Security:** Ship Verifier never judges security — it directs Composer to invoke the Sonnet gate; Sonnet closes its own findings per § Fix-closure rule.

## Critical Reviewer auto-invoke (Grok — Dan 2026-07-08)

Dispatch exactly ONE read-only Task (`subagent_type: "generalPurpose"`, `model: "grok-4.5-fast-xhigh"`, `readonly: true`) BEFORE finalizing or presenting, when ANY of:

- New `.cursor/rules/` file, or an edit changing >30 lines of an existing rule/protocol file
- A plan with ≥3 phases or touching ≥5 files is about to be presented for approval
- A new gate, model role, subagent lane, or recurring workflow is being proposed
- An architecture decision with ≥2 competing options is being put to Dan
- Dan says "grok review" or "devil's advocate"

Never auto-invoke for: routine code/UI edits, bug fixes, deploys, security review (Sonnet owns it), rule tweaks ≤10 lines, or executing an already-reviewed plan. One run per decision — rerun only on material plan change. Evidence: completion report must cite the Task id + model line (same standard as security gate) or the review = NOT RUN. Full role spec: `MODEL_DOSSIER.md` tag `critical-reviewer`.

**Freeze check (D-16):** before approving any new gate, role, workflow, or abstraction, verify the proposal against `PROJECT_STATUS/HARNESS_V1_FREEZE.md` reopening criteria and apply the D-14 evidence-pairing and D-15 deletion/80-20 tests.

## Work Verifier auto-invoke (Fable 5 — tier 3 only, Dan 2026-07-08)

Dispatch exactly ONE read-only Task (`model: "claude-fable-5-thinking-high"`) ONLY when: (1) a phase of a Fable-authored product/architecture spec with semantic drift tripwires completes — before phase N+1 (spec's own gate note, e.g. `docs/location-first-transition-spec.md`, is authoritative); (2) the Ship Verifier escalates ambiguity/architecture concerns; (3) Dan says "fable verify" / "fable check". NOT per-ship (Ship Verifier owns that), NOT for mechanical checklist phases, away batches, routine T2+, or red-gate diagnosis (Sonnet 2-fail owns that). Fix loop: § Fix-closure rule (1 cycle, then Dan). Spec-phase completion reports MUST include a `work-verifier:` line — Task id, or `NOT RUN — phase N+1 blocked until it runs`. Full spec: `MODEL_DOSSIER.md` tag `work-verifier`.

**Verify-only (Dan 2026-07-09):** Fable never edits files, commits, or runs the ship loop — same standing as Sonnet diagnose-only. Only Composer 2.5 implements; Fable verifies Composer's work. When Fable finds issues: Composer fixes, Fable re-verifies per § Fix-closure; affected work ships only after Fable confirms correct.
